title.narrative: NURTURING CARE AND PARENTING PROGRAMMES

description.narrative: By 2023, an increased number of communities, families, parents and caregivers are reached through nurturing and parenting programmes., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, all five Gulf countries have increased coverage of comprehensive, integrated early childhood development (ECD) services and nurturing care practices.

title.narrative: By 2023, an increased number of communities, families, parents and caregivers are reached through nurturing and parentingprogrammes.

description.narrative: COVID-induced restrictions and lockdowns amplified the need for support to parents to provide appropriate nurturing environment for their children. In all GAO countries – UAE, KSA, Kuwait and Qatar, UNICEF worked with government partners and provided support to parents through campaigns, online platforms, and development of parenting programs.; Support to service providers’ was also provided through capacity building interventions and online platforms to enable them to reach to communities, families, parents and caregivers on nurturing and responsive caregiving to the youngest children. Through these two-pronged approach, UNICEF has reached over 7 million parents and caregivers in GAO countries in 2021. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
